<!-- begin paragraph -->
<tr>
<td width=3D"15%" valign=3D"top">
<!-- Add marginal notes below -->
<i>
<a name=3D"PPF">
Percent Point Function
</a>
</i>
</td>
<td valign=3D"TOP" width=3D"85%">
<!-- Add main text below -->
The binomial percent point function does not exist in simple
closed form.  It is computed numerically.  Note that because
this is a discrete distribution that is only defined for integer
values of <i>x</i>, the percent point function is not smooth in the
way the percent point function typically is for a continuous
distribution.
<p>
The following is the plot of the binomial percent point function
with the same values of <i>p</i> as the pdf plots above.
</p><p>
<img src=3D"https://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/eda/section3/gif/binpp=
f4.gif" alt=3D"plot of the binomial percent point function">

</p></td>
</tr>
<!-- end paragraph -->

